The paper focuses on the use of deep learning algorithms for network analysis and performance, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The platform presented, Net2Vec, is designed to capture and process large amounts of network data in real-time, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of Net2Vec for traffic classification and network performance analysis, which are topics related to computer security (cs.CR) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper showcases the use of deep learning for profiling network users, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
